[[File:Nojiri in Miyazaki Prefecture.png|thumb|right|Location of Nojiri in Miyazaki]]
{{nihongo|'''Nojiri'''|<U+91CE><U+5C3B><U+753A>|Nojiri-ch<U+014D>}} is a [[towns of Japan|town]] located in [[Nishimorokata District, Miyazaki|Nishimorokata District]], [[Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki]], [[Japan]].

As of [[2003]], the town has an estimated [[population]] of 8,705 and the [[population density|density]] of 97.96 persons per km<U+00B2>. The total area is 88.86 km<U+00B2>.

A planned [[Merger and dissolution of municipalities of Japan|merger of municipalities]] will be implemented on [[March 23]], [[2010]]. Two municipalities in Nishimorokata District, Nojiri and [[Takaharu, Miyazaki|Takaharu]], will merge into the city of [[Kobayashi, Miyazaki|Kobayashi]]. Nishimorokata District will cease to exist.<ref name="Plannedmerge">http://www.kokudo.or.jp/new/cities/sub/kyusyu/45.htm</ref>

